WEBVTT

00:01.446 --> 00:03.079
Hey, cap'n, got a second?

00:03.113 --> 00:05.848
- It's "Captain."
- What did I say?

00:05.849 --> 00:08.483
"Cap'n,"
like cap'n crunch.

00:08.517 --> 00:09.818
All right,
but to be fair,

00:09.818 --> 00:11.352
cap'n crunch
was a war hero

00:11.353 --> 00:12.954
and the primary
male role model

00:12.955 --> 00:15.890
in my house,
growing up, so...

00:15.924 --> 00:18.259
Anyways, cap-tain,
you know

00:18.260 --> 00:19.927
that jewelry store robbery
down by grand army Plaza?

00:19.961 --> 00:22.596
- Mm-hmm.
- I know who did it... Dustin Whitman.

00:22.597 --> 00:24.265
I put him in Rikers
two years ago.

00:24.266 --> 00:25.566
He just got out,
and the crime scene

00:25.567 --> 00:27.368
matches his M.O. perfectly.

00:27.369 --> 00:29.303
Okay, what do we got?

00:29.338 --> 00:32.707
Well, security cam
shows a male suspect, 5'9"...

00:32.741 --> 00:34.309
Wearing a black ski mask.

00:34.310 --> 00:35.877
He bypassed
the McConnell alarm

00:35.878 --> 00:37.445
by using
the magnetic kill switch.

00:37.446 --> 00:39.748
And he only stole diamonds,
nothing over two carats.

00:39.782 --> 00:41.349
Yeah, exactly.
How'd you know?

00:41.383 --> 00:44.385
I'm a Detective.
It's what I do.

00:45.720 --> 00:47.455
I'm just kidding.
I need a lot more information.

00:47.456 --> 00:49.123
But that would've been
a great exit line, right?

00:49.157 --> 00:50.424
The crime techs
aren't done yet,

00:50.425 --> 00:51.892
but I'm 100% sure
it's Whitman.

00:51.893 --> 00:53.327
Well, let's see
what kind of physical evidence

00:53.328 --> 00:55.395
they turn up,
and then we can talk arrest.

00:55.396 --> 00:58.232
Actually,
hilarious story.

00:58.266 --> 01:01.435
So that is Dustin Whitman.

01:01.469 --> 01:04.604
You already arrested him?
With insufficient evidence?

01:06.039 --> 01:08.440
By law, we have 48 hours
to find that evidence,

01:08.441 --> 01:10.108
or we have to let him go.

01:10.142 --> 01:11.576
You just started the clock.

01:15.379 --> 01:17.680
What's up
with this emergency meeting?

01:17.681 --> 01:20.581
Whoa, Detective Santiago.

01:20.615 --> 01:22.415
Big date tonight.
How do I look?

01:22.450 --> 01:24.317
Well, I think you look...

01:25.987 --> 01:28.254
Sorry, that was supposed
to be a catcall.

01:28.255 --> 01:29.789
I don't know
how this works.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.858
Hey, is this why you were
getting makeup tips

01:31.859 --> 01:33.727
from the prostitute
in the holding cell?

01:33.761 --> 01:35.929
I just wanted to know
how she got such smoky eyes.

01:35.930 --> 01:38.665
Turns out
it was an std rash.

01:38.700 --> 01:39.700
Detective Peralta
has made a collar

01:39.701 --> 01:41.068
in the jewelry store heist.

01:41.102 --> 01:42.703
- Way to go, jakey.
- Ah, that's okay.

01:42.704 --> 01:44.104
No. He didn't get
sufficient evidence

01:44.105 --> 01:45.405
to make it stick,
so we have

01:45.406 --> 01:47.641
the next 48 hours
to fix his mistake.

01:47.675 --> 01:49.209
Damn it, Jake.

01:49.243 --> 01:52.012
What evidence did you have
when you arrested this guy?

01:52.013 --> 01:53.580
Some pretty ironclad stuff.

01:53.581 --> 01:56.216
Dustin, it's been a while.

01:56.217 --> 01:58.152
Mind if I ask you
a few questions?

01:58.186 --> 02:01.522
Well, well, well,
if it isn't joke Peralta.

02:01.523 --> 02:03.582
That's it, you're under arrest.

02:03.592 --> 02:04.858
Case closed?

02:04.893 --> 02:07.060
If we don't find
something conclusive,

02:07.095 --> 02:08.261
it jeopardizes the case

02:08.262 --> 02:09.963
and opens the department up
to a lawsuit.

02:09.964 --> 02:11.298
So cancel your plans.

02:11.333 --> 02:12.600
We're here
until this is over.

02:12.634 --> 02:14.935
- Damn it, Peralta.
- Ow!

02:14.969 --> 02:16.270
I know everyone's mad
at Peralta

02:16.271 --> 02:19.606
for ruining their weekend.

02:19.607 --> 02:20.640
But?

02:20.674 --> 02:21.808
That was it.

02:21.809 --> 02:22.942
I was just demonstrating

02:22.943 --> 02:25.846
for Detective Peralta
what a fact is.

